In [[computer graphics]], '''addressability''' is the capability of a display surface or [[storage]] device to accommodate a specified number of uniquely identifiable points.   
In micrographics, '''addressability''' is the capability of a specified [[field frame]] to contain a specific number of uniquely identifiable points. 

''Note:''  The addressability is usually specified as the number of identifiable horizontal points by the number of identifiable vertical points, such as 3000 by 4000.

''This article contains material from the [[w:Federal Standard 1037C|Federal Standard 1037C]], which, as a [[w:work of the United States Government|work of the United States Government]], is in the [[w:public domain|public domain]].''